00:07:12.250 --> 00:07:14.410
Number one, keyboard feet.

00:07:14.410 --> 00:07:16.320
Have you ever wondered
what those little feet

00:07:16.320 --> 00:07:18.840
that extend out of the back
of your keyboard are for?

00:07:18.840 --> 00:07:20.900
Most of us, like myself included,

00:07:20.900 --> 00:07:24.100
assume they exist for ergonomics,
just to make the keyboard

00:07:24.100 --> 00:07:25.720
more comfortable to type on.

00:07:25.720 --> 00:07:27.381
However, this isn't entirely true.

00:07:27.381 --> 00:07:30.520
It turns out that feet under
keyboards have been mandatory

00:07:30.520 --> 00:07:32.220
since the beginning of the 80s,

00:07:32.220 --> 00:07:35.180
when the International
Organization for Standardization

00:07:35.180 --> 00:07:36.720
stipulated that it should be possible

00:07:36.720 --> 00:07:39.200
to adjust the rear
height of all keyboards.

00:07:39.200 --> 00:07:41.550
Back then, people were
used to typing at height

00:07:41.550 --> 00:07:43.320
with machines such as typewriters,

00:07:43.320 --> 00:07:45.110
so the feet were meant
to adjust the keyboard

00:07:45.110 --> 00:07:47.780
to a higher angle that
people were more used to.

00:07:47.780 --> 00:07:49.570
However, nowadays they are only important

00:07:49.570 --> 00:07:51.610
for people who can't type blind.

00:07:51.610 --> 00:07:53.610
When the keys are extended,
people who have to

00:07:53.610 --> 00:07:56.380
look at the keys, and typically
use two fingers to type,

00:07:56.380 --> 00:07:58.070
have a better view of the keys,

00:07:58.070 --> 00:08:01.020
so it's advantageous for them
to have the feet extended.

00:08:01.020 --> 00:08:03.730
However, a lot of people
nowadays can type blind,

00:08:03.730 --> 00:08:06.300
and in this case, extending
the feet on keyboards

00:08:06.300 --> 00:08:08.888
isn't much use, it can
actually be harmful.

00:08:08.888 --> 00:08:11.580
If your a blind typer, and
don't have to look at the keys

00:08:11.580 --> 00:08:14.270
when typing, then extending
the feet can put your wrists

00:08:14.270 --> 00:08:16.470
at risk if they are angled back too far.

00:08:16.470 --> 00:08:19.640
For this reason, blind typers
should keep the feet retracted

00:08:19.640 --> 00:08:21.290
and use a flat keyboard.

00:08:21.290 --> 00:08:22.990
Various studies have even demonstrated

00:08:22.990 --> 00:08:25.650
a beneficial effect on the
wrists when angling the keyboard

00:08:25.650 --> 00:08:27.690
with a flat or negative incline.

00:08:27.690 --> 00:08:29.690
So, if your a proficient blind typer,

00:08:29.690 --> 00:08:31.838
then keep those keyboard feet retracted.

